description:
&lt;p&gt;We have exciting opportunities for highly motivated, enthusiastic Support Worker to work with the Rapid Response team at London Road Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves visiting patients in their own home, and supporting them with personal care and activities of daily living with a rehabilitation focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team focus on preventing admissions facilitating earlier discharges with Discharge to Assess pathway 1 and pathway 2, and therefore it is desirable that you have a keen interest and some experience rehabilitation and/or community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also have experience of care, nursing skills and using Information technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can demonstrate good communication skills, have the ability to plan and organise competent, evidence based clinical care delivery we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to travel across a wide geographical area is essential for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elaine Wesley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated Community Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;e.wesley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07795 527540&lt;/p&gt;
